social_posts.post_text: I feel just like a rockstar 🎸
I’m so honored that my Mountain Magic Christmas was the most viewed TV movie of the year! I feel so humbled, yet proud. Thank you! @televisionacad ❤️

From @dollywood to Hollywood, Tony Chase was so creative with all the embellishments on my gowns. I love looking at his sketches for the intricate beadwork. I wore this blue dress on tour in the 1990s, and the lavender and purple one for the premiere of Steel Magnolias in Louisiana in 1989. My new book, ‘Behind The Seams: My Life In Rhinestones’ gives a glimpse at all my favorite looks throughout the years and it’s available for pre-order now 💘
Still got time to turn it all around ❤️

I’ve always wanted a reason to sing “Magic Man” by @heartofficial and it was one of my first choices for the album. I was so happy that @annwilson agreed to sing it with me. Nobody can out sing Ann, but I gave it my darndest, and we added a few lines that were not in the original. We wanted to have a few things that made it seem like ours. Hope I’ve made you proud. I think it’s magic!
I love you, London #livefromlondon

I am so excited to see the response ‘Bygones’ is receiving! To debut at #1 on the Rock charts is such a thrill for me, and it makes it even sweeter to share this with @robhalfordlegacy, @nikkisixxpixx, and @john5official. I also have to recognize my co producer on the album and co writer on this song, Kent Wells, who helped me bring this song to life. I am a happy girl today!
Let bygones, be bygones 🎶
Blondes have more fun, just ask @parishilton 💕

I've always believed that not all Barbies come from Malibu; sometimes they come from the holler too! In my new book ‘Behind the Seams,’ I share the story of how this cute gingham and fishnets number came to life for my ‘Backwoods Barbie’ album. It made me feel like a real-life country Barbie, and it's one of my favorites! Pre-order ‘Behind The Seams: My Life In Rhinestones’ now 💗

The music I grew up on inspired my own recordings in the new millennium. In 2002, Chicago-based designer Bambi Breakstone painted elements of my life on this spectacular leather jacket. I love how she folds in the mountains, trees, and of course, lots and lots of rhinestones! The stories of how my fashion came to be are just as striking—or shocking!—as my outfits themselves, if you can believe it, and I share hundreds of them inside ‘Behind the Seams: My Life in Rhinestones’. Available for pre-order now ✨
The higher the hair, the closer to heaven ❤️

Does it get any better than singing “Let It Be” with @paulmccartney who wrote the song? Not only that, he played piano! Well, it did get even better when @ringostarrmusic joined in on drums, @mrpeterframpton on guitar and @mickfleetwoodofficial playing percussion. I mean, seriously, how much better does it get?
